              margin-top: 2px !important;">
              The legacy of Pope Francis
        </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/latin-americas-first-pontiff-legacy-mercy-reform-resistance.png" alt="Latin America’s First Pontiff Leaves Behind a Legacy of Mercy, Reform, and Resistance" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Latin America’s First Pontiff Leaves Behind a Legacy of Mercy, Reform, and Resistance. Credits: AFP Photo</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          Pope Francis, born Jorge Mario Bergoglio, passed away on April 21, 2025. He was a historic figure long before his death. He became the first Latin American pope and the first pontiff in modern history to succeed a living pope (after Benedict XVI resigned in 2013). Their coexisting roles as Pope and Pope Emeritus were unprecedented in the last 600 years.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          During his 12-year papacy, he gained a reputation for his humility and dedication to serving the poor and vulnerable. He pushed for reforms within the Vatican and emerged as a global voice on climate change and inequality. He earned international respect, especially in the Muslim world, for his <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-22-04-2025-h2-5-support-of-palestinians?source=website" target="_blank">support of Palestinians</a>.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          However, many American conservatives questioned his criticism of nationalism and his vocal opposition to harsh immigration policies. Vice President J.D. Vance had a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-22-04-2025-h2-6-public-spat?source=website" target="_blank">public spat</a> with the late Pope, though the two met privately just hours before his death. On the other side, some progressives argue he didn’t go far enough, especially on LGBTQ+ rights and women’s reproductive freedoms. Ukrainians, too, expressed frustration over his <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-22-04-2025-h2-7-repeated-calls-for-peace?source=website" target="_blank">repeated calls for peace</a>, which they saw as overlooking Russian aggression.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          See his <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-22-04-2025-h2-8-legacy-in-pictures?source=website" target="_blank">legacy in pictures</a>.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
