              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">EU isn’t messing around</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5"><strong>Summary: Ursula von der Leyen says Europe will enforce digital laws fairly, even against the biggest names in tech.</strong></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Ursula von der Leyen (European Commission President) said the EU will apply its digital laws to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-22-04-2025-h3-9-all-tech-companies-equally?source=website" target="_blank">all tech companies equally</a>, no matter how powerful they are or who runs them. This comes amid ongoing criticism over the EU’s digital reforms, particularly the Digital Services Act (DSA) and Digital Markets Act (DMA), which aim to protect user rights and ensure fair competition.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">JD Vance has previously threatened to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-22-04-2025-h3-10-withdraw-the-us-from-nato?source=website" target="_blank">withdraw the US from NATO</a> if the EU were to enforce these laws, arguing that it would stifle innovation in Europe. However, Von der Leyen said she will uphold the rulebook against any company regardless of the outside pressure.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">In its first response, the EU has opened cases against TikTok, X, Apple, and Meta. The EU antitrust chief, Teresa Ribera, noted that a decision on whether Apple and Meta have breached tech rules to curb their market power will be issued in the coming weeks. Both companies could face modest fines if found in breach of the DMA.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
